## Data distribution

replot(data = df, x = raw name, y = column name, hue = color for each data, kind = 'scatter')

- Option of "kind"

    scatter: default

    line



```python
sns.relplot(data = raw, x = 'tip', y = 'total_bill')
```

<pre>
<seaborn.axisgrid.FacetGrid at 0x1916f1edd60>
</pre>
<img src="data:image/png;base64,"/>


```python
sns.relplot(data = raw, x = 'tip', y = 'total_bill', kind = 'line')
```

<pre>
<seaborn.axisgrid.FacetGrid at 0x1916a0995e0>
</pre>
<img src="data:image/png;base64,"/>


```python
sns.relplot(data = raw, x = 'tip', y = 'total_bill', hue = 'sex')
```

<pre>
<seaborn.axisgrid.FacetGrid at 0x1916f28eb20>
</pre>

## Relation 

jointplot(data = df, x = raw name, y = column name, kind = 'scatter')

    option of kind:

        scatter: default

        reg: point + regression

        kde: cummulative distribution chart like map



```python
sns.jointplot(data = raw, x = 'tip', y = 'total_bill')
```

<pre>
<seaborn.axisgrid.JointGrid at 0x1916f28e880>
</pre>
<img src="data:image/png;base64,"/>


```python
sns.jointplot(data = raw, x = 'tip', y = 'total_bill', kind = 'kde')
```

<pre>
<seaborn.axisgrid.JointGrid at 0x1916f52d100>
</pre>
<img src="data:image/png;base64,"/>


```python
sns.jointplot(data = raw, x = 'tip', y = 'total_bill', kind = 'reg')
```

<pre>
<seaborn.axisgrid.JointGrid at 0x1916f6663d0>
</pre>
<img src="data:image/png;base64,"/>


```python
sns.jointplot(data = raw, x = 'tip', y = 'total_bill', kind = 'hex')
```

<pre>
<seaborn.axisgrid.JointGrid at 0x1916fe32dc0>
</pre>

## Heat Map

heatmap(data = df)

```python
sns.heatmap(data = df)
```

</pre>

```python
sns.heatmap(data = df, 
           annot = True, fmt = '.2f')
```

<AxesSubplot:xlabel='size', ylabel='day'>
</pre>
<img src="data:image/png;base64,"/>


